The paper discusses a visual analysis tool for sequence-to-sequence models, which are commonly used for natural language processing tasks such as machine translation. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also involves deep learning methods, which suggests categories such as cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The visual analysis tool involves interaction with the model, which could fall under cs.CV (Computer Vision). Finally, the paper aims to detect model errors, which could fall under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
